---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig, buyerFaqs } from "../site";
import { buildFaqSchema } from "../lib/schema";
import "../styles/home-v8.css";

const faqSchema = buildFaqSchema([...buyerFaqs]);

// "Not a founder?" routing — investors / corporate / operators
const subAudiences = [
  {
    title: "Investors & funds.",
    body: "Diagnose growth across a portfolio in two weeks. Same framework, applied across companies.",
    href: "/resources/vc-portfolio-growth-diagnosis",
    label: "VC Portfolio Diagnosis"
  },
  {
    title: "Corporate & accelerator partners.",
    body: "Workshops, keynote talks, and programme advisory for cohorts and innovation teams.",
    href: "/speaking",
    label: "Speaking & workshops"
  },
  {
    title: "Operators, advisors & referrers.",
    body: "Refer a founder, come on the podcast, or partner on a deal. Drop a line.",
    href: "/contact",
    label: "Get in touch"
  }
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="We Scale Startups — Fractional CMO for Post-PMF B2B SaaS & AI"
  description="Fractional CMO who installs a repeatable growth system in 90 days, for post-PMF B2B SaaS and AI founders doing £1–10M ARR."
  path="/"
  schema={faqSchema}
  bodyClass="page-home-v8"
>
  {/* ============ HERO — the problem, the promise, the proof ============ */}
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="shell">
      <span class="hero-badge"><span class="dot"></span> Fractional CMO · Post-PMF B2B SaaS &amp; AI</span>
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div>
          <h1>Your pipeline shouldn't depend on <span class="hl">you running it</span>.</h1>
          <p class="lede">We install the acquisition system your team can run <strong>without the founder in every decision</strong> — in 90 days, for the cost of a senior hire's first quarter.</p>

          <div class="step-chips">
            <a href="/services/growth-diagnosis" class="step-chip"><span class="n">01</span> Diagnose</a>
            <a href="/services/90-day-growth-sprint" class="step-chip"><span class="n">02</span> Sprint</a>
            <a href="/services/acquisition-system-build" class="step-chip"><span class="n">03</span> Build</a>
            <a href="/services/fractional-cmo" class="step-chip"><span class="n">04</span> Embed</a>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-ctas">
            <a href={siteConfig.bookingUrl} class="btn-primary">{siteConfig.bookingLabel} <span>→</span></a>
            <a href={siteConfig.scorecardUrl} class="hero-cta-alt">Or take the 5-min scorecard →</a>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-trust">
            <div class="trust"><span class="trust-v counter" data-target="18" data-suffix="M+" data-prefix="£">£18M+</span><span class="trust-l">Revenue<br />influenced</span></div>
            <div class="trust"><span class="trust-v counter" data-target="6" data-suffix="M+" data-prefix="£">£6M+</span><span class="trust-l">Paid spend<br />managed</span></div>
            <div class="trust"><span class="trust-v counter" data-target="479" data-suffix="+">479+</span><span class="trust-l">Founder<br />sessions</span></div>
            <div class="trust"><span class="trust-v counter" data-target="4.93" data-decimals="2">4.93<span style="font-size:0.55em;color:var(--ink-4);font-weight:500;">/5</span></span><span class="trust-l">GrowthMentor<br />rating</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Diagnostic widget — with tab switcher */}
        <aside class="diag-card glow-card">
          <div class="diag-tabs" role="tablist">
            <button class="diag-tab active" data-tab="saas" role="tab">B2B SaaS</button>
            <button class="diag-tab" data-tab="fintech" role="tab">Fintech</button>
            <button class="diag-tab" data-tab="healthtech" role="tab">Healthtech</button>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-head">
            <span class="diag-head-l">Growth Diagnostic — Live Sample</span>
            <span class="diag-head-r" id="diag-wk">WK 01/12</span>
          </div>
          <div class="diag-title" id="diag-title">What 20 minutes looks like.</div>
          <div class="diag-sub" id="diag-sub">A real diagnosis from a recent call. Yours follows the same shape, with your numbers.</div>
          <div class="diag-metrics">
            <div><div class="m-label">Pipeline today</div><div class="m-val" data-m="now">£42k<span class="unit">/wk</span></div><div class="m-foot" data-m="flat">— flat 6 wks</div></div>
            <div><div class="m-label">12-wk projection</div><div class="m-val violet" data-m="proj">£128k<span class="unit">/wk</span></div><div class="m-foot up" data-m="growth">▲ 3.0× compounding</div></div>
            <div><div class="m-label">Bottleneck</div><div class="m-val violet" data-m="bn">Acq.</div><div class="m-foot" data-m="conf">88% conf.</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="chart-row" id="chart">
            <div class="bar dim" style="height:38%"></div>
            <div class="bar dim" style="height:42%"></div>
            <div class="bar dim" style="height:36%"></div>
            <div class="bar dim" style="height:40%"></div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:48%"></div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:58%"></div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:68%"></div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:78%"></div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:88%"></div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:100%"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="constraints" id="constraints">
            <div class="constraint"><span class="constraint-name"><span class="constraint-n">01</span><span class="constraint-text"><strong>Positioning</strong><span data-c="01">ICP clear · category owned</span></span></span><span class="tag ok" data-t="01">Healthy</span></div>
            <div class="constraint bn"><span class="constraint-name"><span class="constraint-n">02</span><span class="constraint-text"><strong>Acquisition</strong><span data-c="02">Single-source channel</span></span></span><span class="tag bad" data-t="02">Bottleneck</span></div>
            <div class="constraint"><span class="constraint-name"><span class="constraint-n">03</span><span class="constraint-text"><strong>Conversion</strong><span data-c="03">Demo → SQL leak</span></span></span><span class="tag watch" data-t="03">Watch</span></div>
            <div class="constraint"><span class="constraint-name"><span class="constraint-n">04</span><span class="constraint-text"><strong>Reporting</strong><span data-c="04">Weekly cadence trusted</span></span></span><span class="tag ok" data-t="04">Healthy</span></div>
            <div class="constraint"><span class="constraint-name"><span class="constraint-n">05</span><span class="constraint-text"><strong>Team ownership</strong><span data-c="05">Founder-dependent</span></span></span><span class="tag watch" data-t="05">Watch</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="verdict" id="verdict"><strong>Verdict.</strong> Run a 90-day sprint against <em>acquisition</em>.</div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ LOGO WALL — credentials ============ */}
  <section class="logo-wall">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="logo-wall-label">Trusted by founders, programmes &amp; platforms</div>
      <div class="logo-row-groups reveal">
        <div class="logo-group">
          <p class="logo-group-label">Startup programmes &amp; mentoring</p>
          <div class="logo-row">
            <a href="https://startup.google.com/" class="logo-item" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="Google for Startups — mentor">
              <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/google.webp" alt="Google for Startups" width="130" height="30" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
              <span class="logo-meta">Mentor</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://www.techstars.com" class="logo-item" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="Techstars — mentor and speaker">
              <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/techstars.webp" alt="Techstars" width="130" height="30" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
              <span class="logo-meta">Mentor &amp; speaker</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-space-agency" class="logo-item" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="UK Space Agency — startup ecosystem support">
              <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/uksa.webp" alt="UK Space Agency" width="130" height="30" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
              <span class="logo-meta">Ecosystem support</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="logo-group">
          <p class="logo-group-label">Guest lecturing &amp; teaching</p>
          <div class="logo-row">
            <a href="https://www.jbs.cam.ac.uk/" class="logo-item" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="Cambridge Judge Business School — guest lecturer">
              <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/cambridge.webp" alt="Cambridge Judge Business School" width="130" height="30" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
              <span class="logo-meta">Guest lecturer</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://www.imperial.ac.uk/business-school" class="logo-item" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="Imperial College Business School — speaker">
              <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/imperial.webp" alt="Imperial College Business School" width="130" height="30" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
              <span class="logo-meta">Speaker</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://generalassemb.ly/" class="logo-item" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="General Assembly — growth teaching">
              <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/general-assembly.webp" alt="General Assembly" width="130" height="30" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
              <span class="logo-meta">Growth teaching</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="logo-group">
          <p class="logo-group-label">Founder reviews</p>
          <div class="logo-row">
            <a href="https://app.growthmentor.com/mentors/daniel-johnson" class="logo-item" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="GrowthMentor — 4.93 across 479+ sessions">
              <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/growthmentor-v2.jpg" alt="GrowthMentor" width="130" height="30" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
              <span class="logo-meta">★ 4.93 · 479+ sessions</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://mentorcruise.com/mentor/danieljohnson/" class="logo-item cred-item" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" aria-label="MentorCruise — Top Mentor, 5.0 out of 5">
              <span class="cred-name">MentorCruise</span>
              <span class="logo-meta">Top Mentor · 5.0/5</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ MANIFESTO — why a system beats heroics ============ */}
  <section class="manifesto">
    <div class="shell">
      <span class="spec-label">The thesis · § 01</span>
      <p class="manifesto-quote reveal">Most post-PMF startups don't have a marketing problem. They have a <em>system problem</em> — every growth decision still routes through the founder.</p>
      <div class="manifesto-grid">
        <div class="belief-card glow-card reveal" data-d="1">
          <span class="belief-n">/01 — Diagnose before spend</span>
          <h4>Name the constraint first.</h4>
          <p>More budget against an unnamed bottleneck buys activity, not pipeline. Every engagement starts by naming the single constraint that's binding growth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="belief-card glow-card reveal" data-d="2">
          <span class="belief-n">/02 — Systems over heroics</span>
          <h4>Install a rhythm, not a hero.</h4>
          <p>A weekly decision cadence your team owns beats a brilliant operator who leaves. We build the operating system, then transfer it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="belief-card glow-card reveal" data-d="3">
          <span class="belief-n">/03 — Built to hand off</span>
          <h4>You shouldn't need us forever.</h4>
          <p>Success is the quarter the system runs without us — channels aligned, reporting trusted, decisions made on schedule, founder out of the loop.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ INTERACTIVE BOTTLENECK FINDER ============ */}
  <section class="bf-section">
    <div class="shell">
      <span class="spec-label">Interactive · § 02 · Find your bottleneck</span>
      <h2 class="section-h">Which constraint sounds <em>like you</em>?</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Click whichever feels closest. We'll show you which engagement matches.</p>

      <div class="bottleneck-finder">
        <div class="bf-grid reveal" id="bf-grid">
          <button class="bf-card" data-bn="positioning"><span class="bf-num">01 / POSITIONING</span><span class="bf-name">Story doesn't land</span><span class="bf-q">Demos go well, pipeline doesn't.</span></button>
          <button class="bf-card active" data-bn="acquisition"><span class="bf-num">02 / ACQUISITION</span><span class="bf-name">One-channel risk</span><span class="bf-q">If it dips, the quarter dips.</span></button>
          <button class="bf-card" data-bn="conversion"><span class="bf-num">03 / CONVERSION</span><span class="bf-name">No playbook</span><span class="bf-q">Every rep improvises.</span></button>
          <button class="bf-card" data-bn="reporting"><span class="bf-num">04 / REPORTING</span><span class="bf-name">Dashboards disagree</span><span class="bf-q">No single weekly view.</span></button>
          <button class="bf-card" data-bn="team"><span class="bf-num">05 / TEAM</span><span class="bf-name">Founder bottleneck</span><span class="bf-q">Every brief routes through you.</span></button>
        </div>

        <div class="bf-result glow-card reveal" id="bf-result">
          <div>
            <div class="bf-result-meta" id="bf-meta">02 · ACQUISITION</div>
            <h4 id="bf-title">One channel carries the funnel.</h4>
            <p id="bf-desc">Diversify before the dip — design the second engine and the weekly decision rule.</p>
            <a class="bf-result-link" id="bf-link" href="/services/acquisition-system-build">Acquisition System Build →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="bf-rec">
            <span class="bf-rec-label">Recommended engagement</span>
            <span class="bf-rec-svc" id="bf-svc">Acquisition System Build</span>
            <span class="bf-rec-meta" id="bf-svc-meta">from £30k · 8–12 weeks · Flagship</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ SERVICES LADDER ============ */}
  <section class="services">
    <div class="shell">
      <span class="spec-label">Four engagements · one ladder · § 03</span>
      <h2 class="section-h">Pick the smallest commitment that answers your <em>biggest</em> question.</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Each engagement installs what the next one needs — diagnosis names the constraint, the sprint tests the move, the build installs the rhythm, embed operates it. Start small, ladder up.</p>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <article class="svc-card glow-card reveal">
          <span class="svc-step">/01</span>
          <span class="svc-title">Growth Diagnosis</span>
          <span class="svc-price">£4k · 1 week</span>
          <div class="svc-desc"><strong>Best for</strong>You're not sure what's blocking pipeline.</div>
          <div class="svc-desc"><strong>What gets built</strong>Constraint map, evidence review, 90-day plan.</div>
          <div class="svc-cta"><a href="/services/growth-diagnosis">Read →</a></div>
        </article>
        <article class="svc-card glow-card reveal" data-d="1">
          <span class="svc-step">/02</span>
          <span class="svc-title">90-Day Growth Sprint</span>
          <span class="svc-price">£15k · 12 weeks</span>
          <div class="svc-desc"><strong>Best for</strong>Focused tests against the named bottleneck this quarter.</div>
          <div class="svc-desc"><strong>What gets built</strong>Experiment backlog, weekly decisions, tested copy.</div>
          <div class="svc-cta"><a href="/services/90-day-growth-sprint">Run →</a></div>
        </article>
        <article class="svc-card flagship glow-card reveal" data-d="2">
          <span class="svc-step">/03 <span class="svc-flag">Flagship</span></span>
          <span class="svc-title">Acquisition System Build</span>
          <span class="svc-price">£30k · 8–12 weeks</span>
          <div class="svc-desc"><strong>Best for</strong>Channels in isolation; you need them as one system.</div>
          <div class="svc-desc"><strong>What gets built</strong>Channel architecture, offer map, reporting, handoff pack.</div>
          <div class="svc-cta"><a href="/services/acquisition-system-build">Build →</a></div>
        </article>
        <article class="svc-card glow-card reveal" data-d="3">
          <span class="svc-step">/04</span>
          <span class="svc-title">Fractional CMO</span>
          <span class="svc-price">£8k/mo · 3-mo min</span>
          <div class="svc-desc"><strong>Best for</strong>Senior growth leadership without a £150k full-time hire.</div>
          <div class="svc-desc"><strong>What gets built</strong>Operating cadence, agency direction, board reporting.</div>
          <div class="svc-cta"><a href="/services/fractional-cmo">Embed →</a></div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ CASE STUDIES ============ */}
  <section class="cases">
    <div class="shell">
      <span class="spec-label">Real engagements · § 04</span>
      <h2 class="section-h">Results, <em>named</em>.</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Every row labelled — paid client engagement vs programme or lecturing — so nothing reads like an implied client when it isn't.</p>
      <div class="case-grid">
        <article class="case-card feature glow-card reveal">
          <span class="case-meta">Paid · Fintech · Fractional CMO</span>
          <h4>Ned</h4>
          <div class="case-sub">Funding platform · Google Ads + SEO overhaul</div>
          <p><strong>500+ sign-ups</strong> in two months from paid search. The team needed to move beyond organic reach and lower the cost of getting users to try the product.</p>
          <div class="case-mini-stats">
            <div><div class="case-stat-v">8.6%</div><div class="case-stat-l">Avg CTR</div></div>
            <div><div class="case-stat-v">500+</div><div class="case-stat-l">Sign-ups · 2mo</div></div>
            <div><div class="case-stat-v">$0.74</div><div class="case-stat-l">Avg CPC</div></div>
          </div>
          <a href="/case-studies/ned" class="case-link">Read the full case study →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="case-card glow-card reveal" data-d="1">
          <span class="case-meta">Paid · Healthtech</span>
          <h4>Healthtech (anon.)</h4>
          <div class="case-sub">Precision medicine · Fractional CMO</div>
          <p>Marketing function <strong>built from zero</strong>. Operating rhythm installed.</p>
          <a href="/case-studies/healthtech-precision-medicine" class="case-link">Read →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="case-card glow-card reveal" data-d="2">
          <span class="case-meta">Paid · Healthtech</span>
          <h4>eQuoo</h4>
          <div class="case-sub">Mental-health app · Fractional CMO</div>
          <p>Clearer <strong>acquisition narrative</strong> and channel hierarchy.</p>
          <a href="/case-studies/equoo" class="case-link">Read →</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ TESTIMONIALS ============ */}
  <section class="testimonials">
    <div class="shell">
      <span class="spec-label">Founder voices · § 05</span>
      <h2 class="section-h">What founders <em>say</em>.</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Paid clients first, mentoring reviews second. All verifiable on request.</p>
      <div class="testim-grid">
        <figure class="testim-card glow-card reveal">
          <span class="testim-mark">"</span>
          <blockquote>The WSS diagnosis named the exact bottleneck we had been debating for months. The 90-day sprint shipped six experiments and gave us a weekly cadence that still runs without Daniel today.</blockquote>
          <cite><strong>James Madia</strong>Founder, Madia · Paid engagement</cite>
        </figure>
        <figure class="testim-card glow-card reveal" data-d="1">
          <span class="testim-mark">"</span>
          <blockquote>Daniel helped us move from scattered founder-led marketing to a clear weekly acquisition rhythm. Within 90 days we had sharper ICP, cleaner reporting, and a campaign system the team could run without everything routing back to the founder.</blockquote>
          <cite><strong>B2B SaaS founder, CEO</strong>Paid engagement · name on request</cite>
        </figure>
        <figure class="testim-card glow-card reveal" data-d="2">
          <span class="testim-mark">"</span>
          <blockquote>Daniel went above and beyond to share tactical feedback and help overhaul our approach to SEO.</blockquote>
          <cite><strong>Dru Riley</strong>Growth mentoring · MentorCruise</cite>
        </figure>
        <figure class="testim-card glow-card reveal" data-d="3">
          <span class="testim-mark">"</span>
          <blockquote>Sharp, practical advice with a clear focus on messaging and positioning. He helped me reframe the problem and target the right audience more effectively.</blockquote>
          <cite><strong>Greg Weinstein</strong>Founder mentoring · MentorCruise</cite>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ ABOUT — with real photos ============ */}
  <section class="about">
    <div class="shell">
      <span class="spec-label">Founder · § 06</span>
      <div class="about-grid">
        <div class="about-photo-stack reveal">
          <div class="about-photo">
            <img src="/images/daniel-headshot-640.webp" alt="Daniel Johnson, founder of We Scale Startups" loading="lazy" width="640" height="640" decoding="async" />
          </div>
          <div class="about-photo-secondary">
            <img src="/images/daniel-aircraft-640.webp" alt="Daniel Johnson — operator-side context" loading="lazy" width="640" height="640" decoding="async" />
          </div>
          <div class="about-photo-caption">Daniel Johnson · Founder, We Scale Startups</div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-content reveal" data-d="1">
          <h2>Why I built <em>this</em>.</h2>
          <p>I'm Daniel Johnson. After 15 years operating inside SaaS, fintech, healthtech and EdTech startups — including two exits — I kept seeing the same pattern: founders with great products, stuck running marketing themselves because nobody else on the team could read the numbers and decide what to scale.</p>
          <p>I built We Scale Startups to be the operator I wished was there. <strong>The work is to diagnose the bottleneck, install the acquisition system, and transfer the weekly rhythm</strong> — so you don't need me forever.</p>
          <ul class="about-creds">
            <div class="label">Track record</div>
            <li>Two operator-side startup exits</li>
            <li>£18M+ revenue influenced</li>
            <li>£6M+ paid acquisition spend</li>
            <li>479+ founder sessions · 4.93/5</li>
            <li>MentorCruise Top Mentor · 5.0/5</li>
            <li>Cambridge Judge · Imperial · Techstars</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ FAQ ============ */}
  <section class="faq">
    <div class="shell">
      <span class="spec-label">Before you book · § 07</span>
      <h2 class="section-h">Questions you'll ask <em>before you book</em>.</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Short answers for teams deciding whether they need more execution, sharper diagnosis, or senior growth ownership.</p>
      <div class="faq-list reveal">
        <details class="faq-item" open>
          <summary><span class="q-num">/01</span><span class="q-text">Who is We Scale Startups for?</span></summary>
          <div class="answer">Post-PMF B2B SaaS and AI startups, typically Seed to Series B, with real traction and inconsistent acquisition. If you're still searching for product-market fit, we're the wrong call — growth marketing won't fix a product problem.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="q-num">/02</span><span class="q-text">How is WSS different from an agency?</span></summary>
          <div class="answer">Agencies are the right choice when the channel plan is clear and you need production capacity. WSS works one level up — naming the bottleneck, aligning channels, installing the weekly decision rhythm, and handing off a system your team (or your agency) can run inside. Many teams need both, often in that order.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="q-num">/03</span><span class="q-text">What does the first call actually cover?</span></summary>
          <div class="answer">20 minutes. Bring your current numbers and the constraint you suspect is binding pipeline. You'll leave with the constraint named in plain English, the next move sketched out, and an honest read on whether WSS is the right call.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="q-num">/04</span><span class="q-text">What does it cost?</span></summary>
          <div class="answer">Four engagements, four price points. Diagnosis from £4k (one week). 90-Day Sprint from £15k. Acquisition System Build from £30k. Fractional CMO from £8k/mo, 3-month minimum. <a href="/pricing">Full pricing →</a></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="q-num">/05</span><span class="q-text">Do you guarantee results?</span></summary>
          <div class="answer">No. Anyone who guarantees marketing outcomes either doesn't understand the work or doesn't intend to do it. What we guarantee is the operating system — a constraint named, a plan to move it, and a weekly rhythm your team can run.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="q-num">/06</span><span class="q-text">Who isn't this for?</span></summary>
          <div class="answer">Pre-PMF startups, founders looking for tactic-of-the-week, teams without internal execution capacity, and volume buyers who want more activity rather than fewer sharper decisions. If that's you, we'll say so on the call and point you somewhere better.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ============ SUB-AUDIENCE ROUTING ============ */}
  <section class="v8-sub-audience" aria-label="Other audiences">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="v8-sub-label">Not a founder?</div>
      <div class="v8-sub-grid reveal">
        {subAudiences.map((a) => (
          <div class="v8-sub-item">
            <h4>{a.title}</h4>
            <p>{a.body}</p>
            <a href={a.href}>{a.label} →</a>
          </div>
        ))}
